text: Barákapuszta is a former village, now a part of Zichyújfalu, Hungary. == Geography == It currently has a population of around 15 (in 2013). Barákapuszta an area of 0.8 km². == History == The settlement founded of 17th century. == References == Category:Villages in Hungary Category:Fejér County Category:17th-century establishments in Europe Category:Establishments in Hungary
title: Barákapuszta
